Array:
=====
=> Array is a linear data structure which stores the fixed number of similar data type elements
=> Array can store primitive data type as well as Objects but it should be of same kind.
=> Array is one of the most used data structure in Java.

 
Advantages of Array:
====================
=> you can randomly access any array elements using indices.
=> It can represent the multiple elements of same type with single name;
=> You can implement various data structures such as LinkedList,Stack,Queue using Array data structure.


DisAdvantages of Array;
======================
=> you need to know number of elements going to store in array in advance
=> you can't modify the array once the size is defined.
=> Insertion and Deletion are quite Costly Operation in array as we need to shift elements.